### vTaskDelay vs delay()

This is the most important concept in FreeRTOS:

```c
/* Arduino delay() — WRONG in production */
delay(1000);
/* CPU does NOTHING for 1 second.
   No other tasks can run.
   WiFi packets missed.
   MQTT drops.
   Button presses missed. */

/* FreeRTOS vTaskDelay — CORRECT */
vTaskDelay(pdMS_TO_TICKS(1000));
/* This task sleeps for 1 second.
   CPU is RELEASED to other tasks.
   WiFi keeps running.
   MQTT keeps running.
   Other tasks execute normally. */
```

### PC Analogy for vTaskDelay

```
vTaskDelay is like pressing Minimize on a window.
Your program is still open — just not using the screen.
Other programs get to use the computer.
After 1 second Windows brings your window back.

delay() is like one program FREEZING your entire PC.
Mouse does not move. Nothing responds.
After 1 second it unfreezes.
```

### Monitoring Task Health

```c
/* Check how much stack is left
   If this gets close to zero — increase stack size */
UBaseType_t watermark = uxTaskGetStackHighWaterMark(NULL);
ESP_LOGI(TAG, "Stack watermark: %u bytes remaining", watermark);

/* If watermark < 256 bytes — danger zone
   Increase stack by 512 or 1024 bytes */
```

