## One Line Summary

> "Priority inversion is when a low priority intern accidentally blocks the CEO — because a medium priority manager keeps running and prevents the intern from finishing. FreeRTOS mutexes fix this automatically by temporarily promoting the intern to CEO level. This exact bug crashed a NASA spacecraft on Mars in 1997."

```
Task HIGH  (priority 10) — needs resource X
Task LOW   (priority  1) — holds resource X and cannot release it
Task MED   (priority  5) — running and not blocked

What happens:
Task HIGH waits for resource X
Task LOW cannot run because Task MED keeps running
Task HIGH effectively runs at LOW priority
This is priority inversion — a bug in many production systems

Fix: Use mutexes — they implement priority inheritance
     automatically in FreeRTOS.
```

