## 7. Debugging FreeRTOS

### Check Stack Usage

```c
/* Add to any task to see how much stack is left */
void my_task(void *arg) {
    while (1) {
        ESP_LOGI(TAG, "Stack watermark: %u",
                 uxTaskGetStackHighWaterMark(NULL));
        vTaskDelay(pdMS_TO_TICKS(5000));
    }
}
/* If watermark < 256 — increase stack size by 1024 */
```

### Enable Stack Overflow Detection

In menuconfig:

```
Component config
  --> FreeRTOS
    --> Kernel
      --> Stack overflow detection method
        --> Method 2 (most reliable)
```

When a task overflows its stack — you see:

```
***ERROR*** A stack overflow in task my_task has been detected.
```

### List All Running Tasks

```c
#include "freertos/FreeRTOS.h"
#include "freertos/task.h"

void print_task_list(void) {
    char buf[512];
    vTaskList(buf);
    ESP_LOGI(TAG, "Task list:\n%s", buf);
}
```

Output:

```
Name          State  Priority  Stack  Num
sensor_task   R      5         1800   3
display_task  B      5         1600   4
log_task      B      3         1200   5
IDLE          R      0         900    1
```

